trans-unit.source: getMemberGroups
trans-unit.target: getMemberGroups

trans-unit.source: Call the <embeddedLabel>getMemberGroups</embeddedLabel> function on a user, contact, group, or service principal to get the groups that it is a member of.
trans-unit.target: Call the <embeddedLabel>getMemberGroups</embeddedLabel> function on a user, contact, group, or service principal to get the groups that it is a member of.

trans-unit.source: The function is transitive.
trans-unit.target: The function is transitive.

trans-unit.source: This function takes a single parameter that indicates whether only membership in security enabled groups or whether membership in all groups should be checked.
trans-unit.target: This function takes a single parameter that indicates whether only membership in security enabled groups or whether membership in all groups should be checked.

trans-unit.source: If only membership in security enabled groups is selected, the function can only be called on a user.
trans-unit.target: If only membership in security enabled groups is selected, the function can only be called on a user.

trans-unit.source: It returns a collection that contains the Object IDs of the groups of which the user, contact, group, or service principal is a member.
trans-unit.target: It returns a collection that contains the Object IDs of the groups of which the user, contact, group, or service principal is a member.

trans-unit.source: The operation is transitive, that is, if User A is a member of Group B and Group B is a member of Group C and the function is called on User A and Group C is a group of the type specified in the parameter, Group C will be in the collection returned by the function.
trans-unit.target: The operation is transitive, that is, if User A is a member of Group B and Group B is a member of Group C and the function is called on User A and Group C is a group of the type specified in the parameter, Group C will be in the collection returned by the function.

trans-unit.source: This is different than the <languageKeyword>isMemberOf</languageKeyword> navigation property, which returns only groups in which an entity has direct membership and cannot be filtered to return only security enabled groups.
trans-unit.target: This is different than the <languageKeyword>isMemberOf</languageKeyword> navigation property, which returns only groups in which an entity has direct membership and cannot be filtered to return only security enabled groups.
